Election 2020

How many Minneasota primary voters sent mail ballots?

By Jeff Hargarten
Star Tribune August 9, 2020

Minnesotans requested tenfold more absentee ballots in this primary than 2018, and 21 times 2016's volume.

How elections are conducted in the COVID-19 era is fundamentally altered, resulting in surges of early and mail-in balloting.

Early voting in Minnesota's primaries may indicate the outsized impact absentee balloting may have on November's general election.
